# Alerts & confirmations

## Always use `showAlert`

For confirmations, errors, success messages, and multi-choice prompts, use **`showAlert`** from `@/contexts/AlertContext` via `useAlert()`.

**Do not** use React Native `Alert.alert` or other system alert APIs.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
import { Alert } from 'react-native';
Alert.alert('Title', 'Message', [{ text: 'OK' }]);

// ✅ GOOD
import { useAlert } from '@/contexts/AlertContext';

const { showAlert } = useAlert();

showAlert({
  title: 'Title',
  message: 'Message',
  buttons: [{ text: 'OK' }],
});
```

## Button patterns

- **Single action:** one button (e.g. `Entendido`, `OK`).
- **Confirm / cancel:** pass both; cancel uses `style: 'cancel'`, destructive actions use `style: 'destructive'`.
- **Three or more choices:** list all options in `buttons`; cancel last with `style: 'cancel'`. The alert stacks buttons vertically.

```tsx
showAlert({
  title: 'Eliminar foto',
  message: '¿Seguro que quieres eliminar esta foto?',
  buttons: [
    { text: 'Cancelar', style: 'cancel' },
    { text: 'Eliminar', style: 'destructive', onPress: handleDelete },
  ],
});
```

## Toasts vs alerts

- **`showAlert`:** blocking feedback the user must acknowledge (success after forgot password, delete confirm, errors that need attention).
- **`showInfoToast`:** brief non-blocking feedback (save succeeded, background actions). Do not replace confirms with toasts.

## Provider

`AlertProvider` wraps the app in `app/_layout.tsx`. Any screen under that tree can call `useAlert()`.
